NOTICE REGARDING SALE & SHARING OF PERSONAL DATA FOR TARGETED ADVERTISING
In some states, residents have the right to opt-out of having their personal data sold or shared for targeted advertising purposes.  We do not sell or share personal information as defined under applicable data protection laws and have not done so within the last 12 months.
Whenever the processing operation is carried out in Brazil, the purpose of the processing activity is to offer or provide goods or services or the processing of data of individuals located in Brazil; or the personal data being processed were collected in Brazil according to Section 3 of LGPD (“LGPD Data”), this Policy shall governed according to: (i) the General Data Protection Law, no. 13,709/2018 (hereinafter the "LGPD"), (ii) the Constitution of the Brazilian Federative Republic, article 5, item LXXII; (iii) the Habeas Data Law (hereinafter "Habeas Data"), no. 9,507/1997; and, finally, the (iv) Internet Civil Rights , Law No. 12,965/2014.
When processing LGPD Data, the following principles shall apply:
Purpose
: Personal Data collected must be used for a lawful, legitimate, specific and explicit purpose, which must be informed in advance, in a clear and sufficient manner;
Adequacy
: Processing of Personal Data compatible with the informed purpose;
Need
: Limitation of the processing to the minimum necessary for the accomplishment of its purposes, with the scope of the relevant, proportional and non-excessive data in relation to the purposes of the processing of data;
Free Access:
facilitated and free of charge consultation about the form and duration of the processing, as well as about the integrity of their personal data;
Quality
: accuracy, clarity, relevance and updating of the data, according to the need and for the fulfillment of the purpose of its processing;
Transparency
: clear, accurate and easily accessible information about the carrying out of the processing and the respective processing agents, subject to commercial and industrial secrecy;
Security
: use of technical and administrative measures to protect Personal Data from unauthorized access and accidental or unlawful situations of destruction, loss, alteration, communication or disclosure;
Prevention
: Adoption of measures to prevent the occurrence of damage due to the Processing of Personal Data;
Non-discrimination
: Impossibility of processing for unlawful or abusive discriminatory purposes;
Accountability
: adoption of effective measures capable of proving compliance with the rules of protection of Personal Data and the effectiveness of these measures;
When we process your LGPD Data, you are entitled to:
Obtain confirmation of the existence of processing.
Free access to your Personal Data that has been processed, as provided in Section 9 and 18 of the LGPD.
Correction of incomplete, inaccurate or outdated Personal Data.
Anonymization, blocking or deletion of unnecessary, excessive or processed data in non-compliance with the provisions of the LGPD.
Portability of Personal Data to another service provider or product, upon express request, in accordance with the regulations of the ANPD, in compliance with trade and industrial secrets.
Deletion of Personal Data processed with your consent, except in the cases provided for in Art. 16 of the LGPD;
Information of public and private entities with which we have shared your Personal Data;
Information on the possibility of not providing consent and on the consequences of such a denial;
Withdrawal of consent, pursuant to § 5 of Section 8 of the LGPD;
Submit to the ANPD complaints for violations of the provisions of the Applicable Regulations and the other rules that modify, add or supplement it, on the basis of § 1 of Section 18 of the LGPD.
DATA RETENTION: How Long Will You Use My Personal Data?
We will only retain your personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes we collected it for, including for the purposes of satisfying any legal, accounting, or reporting requirements. To determine the appropriate retention period for personal data, we consider the amount, nature, and sensitivity of the personal data, the potential risk of harm from unauthorized use or disclosure of your personal data, the purposes for which we process your personal data and whether we can achieve those purposes through other means, and the applicable legal requirements.
Details of retention periods for different aspects of your personal data are available in our retention policy which you can request from us by contacting us. More specifically, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, by law we have to keep basic information about our customers for at least 5 years after they cease being customers for tax, financial auditing, and record keeping purposes.
You may have rights under data protection laws in relation to your personal data. Contact us for more information.
